# Image Generation (claude-imagine MCP)

When the user needs an image (hero, icon, product photo, avatar, banner, etc.):

1. **Engineer a prompt** (150–250 words): scene, lighting, atmosphere, camera/lens, color grading, materials, style markers, quality anchors. Comma-separated phrases, not full sentences. No negative terms in the main prompt.
2. **Call the MCP tool** `generate_image` on server `claude-imagine` with the crafted prompt as `description`.
3. **Pick the right type**: ICON, THUMBNAIL, BACKGROUND, TEXTURE (fast); AVATAR, CONTENT, BANNER, PRODUCT (standard); LOGO, HERO, FEATURED (high).
4. **Save** to a sensible `output_path` in the project (default: `generated/<slug>.png`).

Use `list_capabilities` to see configured models and image types.
Use `check_server` before batch generation.
Use `batch_generate` when multiple images are needed at once.

## Never

- Placeholder services (picsum, placehold.it, via.placeholder, lorempixel)
- Empty `src=""` on `<img>` tags
- Skip prompt engineering and pass a one-line description to `generate_image`

## Inline generation while coding

When building HTML/UI and an `<img>` is needed, generate in context using the surrounding theme, palette, and copy — do not defer to stock placeholders.

## Reference

| Tier | Types |
|------|-------|
| Fast | ICON, THUMBNAIL, BACKGROUND, TEXTURE |
| Standard | AVATAR, CONTENT, BANNER, PRODUCT |
| High | LOGO, HERO, FEATURED |
